  "abstract": "On September 14, 1999, the Board published revised proposals for public comment that would permit electronic delivery of federally mandated disclosures under five consumer protection regulations: B (Equal Credit Opportunity), E (Electronic Fund Transfers), M (Consumer Leasing), Z (Truth in Lending), and DD (Truth in Savings). The Board is extending the comment period to give the public additional time to provide comments.",
